                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by cenanorn[/i]
[br]15 sec = 5 ch * 300 mana (generous due to aa and mana pres) = 1500 mana = 10 twitches = 1 min 40 sec minimum chain casting twitch till oom given necro with 3500 mana pool and some aa and mana pres item.

given necro at 200dps 

most normal raids I would estimate at 20 damage dealers at 100dps each

20 people * 100DPS = 2kdps

500k hps for a mob / 2kDPS = 250 seconds with necro twitching

if mob last for 200 seconds necro can do 40000 damage before oom if not twitching
(500k - 40K(necro damage))/ 2kdps from rest of raid gives 230 seconds

thus 20 seconds shorter saving the clerics 6*300 mana = 2100 mana which is a larger than the 1500 that would have been granted via twitching.

The lower a necros DPS then the more applicable twitching.At 150 dps this example would have broke even at mana efficiency.

if 300m for a cheal is too low an estimate then twitching looks even worse

The longer the fight the less applicable twitching is.

 


[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
