                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/06/2003&nbsp;: 09:55:05 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> It does matter how much damage you'd be doing with that mana, twitching low mana clerics is far more worthwhile.  When you're doing mobs that hit for 1600 and quad, the tank NEEDS to be kept up, or else the raid is going to fold like a paper bag in a rainstorm being stepped on by a herd of elephants.  Necromancers have a key role they can play by augmenting a Complete Heal rotation by replenishing mana on any clerics who are running LoM..it happens more rarely in the higher end guilds once the flowing thought items start rolling in, but, even in my guild, we have apps that don't have as good gear to allow them to keep up, or fights where our dps does not match what is needed for the mob, and clerics start to run low on mana...my guild is not high-end by any means, we're merely hitting Teir 2 or 3 PoP bosses and slogging our way thru Ssra, but twitching is a viable route for a necro to do with their mana...hell, I can chain twitch and remain at 80 % mana if i have a bard song playing and SoS up.  No, twitching might not be the most efficient thing, but it is something we can do to save the raid from wiping...a few more CH's where the MT is kept up and the ENTIRE raid is still fighting is better than trying to nuke down the mob, which, at this point in my playing, has too much hp for one person nuking to make too much of a difference if the mob is at 10 %...at 2 %, yes, i can see going all out, but at 10 %, the clerics will need the mana more.  At least, that's just my opinion.  I didn't read the whole post before typing this, but I think DarkZephyr has it stated pretty clearly in his post what you need to know..</span></font></td>
