                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/29/2003&nbsp;: 5:38:17 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> OK lets address these remarks<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">  Please don't try and use the exception to prove a point. Fully magic resistant mobs are few and far between. We all realize that we can't do damage to them and that we should try to contribute in some other way. <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />How about mobs that are immune to poisen only? After putting down all your dots are you just going to wait and reapply them? How often are you actually OOM on raids where you are unable to nuke? Sitting on your mana is not the best way to play any class. <br /> <br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> Twitching is never going to buy a couple minutes.  It takes longer (cast + recast) to transfer 150 mana to a cleric than it takes the cleric to spend 400 (CH, 10-second cast). <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I have actually seen the difference on a 2 cleric rotation. Cleric (1) heals tank, while cleric (2) Meds and is twitched <br />Any one disagree?<br />You can buy a considerable amount of time assisting in this sort of way. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> Twitching is a downtime reducer.  In combat it's not only grossly inefficient, but 99 times out of 100 it's also actually counter productive.  The time it takes to transfer any meaningful amount of mana is time you could spend doing damage and ending the fight. <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />As I said before. If you think your DPS is greater than the entire raid then have at it. The reason why twitching is so inefficient is because it is so damn powerful. <br /><br />Look at it this way. If you are able to assist a cleric to cast 2 additional CH's that is the equivalent of doubling the MT's HP's. <br /><br />Possibly the equivalent of the MT having his defensive dicipline recycled. Do not discount this ability as trivial. <br /><br />Yit<br /><br /><br /><br /></span></font></td>
